FBIS3-16272 "drsov050_b_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Grachev Cancels Trip Due to Yeltsin Absence LD1403183394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403183394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] A working trip by Pavel Grachev, Russian minister of defense, to the troops of the Leningrad military district which was planned for today has been postponed, Yelena Agapova, the minister's spokeswoman, has told ITAR-TASS. She said that the decision to postpone Pavel Grachev's trip was made with a view to ensuring reliable control of the strategic nuclear forces while President Boris Yeltsin, supreme commander, and Mikhail Kolesnik, chief of the general staff, are not in Moscow.
